Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CC (Computational Complexity), and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of artificial intelligence techniques, such as local search, which makes cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a likely sub-category as well. Finally, the paper also discusses the use of geometric concepts, such as chains, which could make cs.CG (Computational Geometry) a possible sub-category.
